SUMMARY:Cherry Blossoms & Riverfront Loop
DESCRIPTION:Portland City Trail Walking Group\n**Let’s meet for a leisurely riverside loop to enjoy Portland’s cherry blossoms at Tom McCall Waterfront Park and stroll both sides of the Willamette River. We’ll walk at a relaxed\, conversational pace with plenty of time for photos.**\n**We’ll meet at Salmon Street Springs fountain in Tom McCall Waterfront Park\, in the plaza along SW Naito just north of the Hawthorne Bridge. From there\, we’ll head north through Waterfront Park toward the cherry trees near the Japanese American Historical Plaza\, between the Burnside and Steel Bridges.**\n**After enjoying the blossoms\, we’ll continue to the Steel Bridge and cross on the lower pedestrian/bike level to the east side of the river. Then we’ll follow the Vera Katz Eastside Esplanade south along the river\, including the floating walkway\, with great views back toward downtown and the bridges.**\n**We’ll cross back over the Willamette on Tilikum Crossing\, Portland’s car‑free “bridge of the people\,” and return north along the west bank paths and sidewalks to Salmon Street Springs\, closing the loop. The full route will be roughly 4.5–5 miles\, mostly flat\, on paved surfaces.**\n**Pace & difficulty:**\n**• Pace: Easy\, social (about 2–2.5 mph) with pauses for photos and regrouping.**\n**• Distance: Approximately 4.5–5 miles.**\n**• Elevation: Essentially flat\, with gentle ramps onto and off of bridges (Steel Bridge and Tilikum Crossing).**\n**• Surfaces: Paved city sidewalks and multi‑use paths\; some areas can be busy with bikes\, so we’ll keep right and stay aware when changing sides.**\n**Logistics:**\n**• Meeting time: 10 am (please arrive a few minutes early so we can start on time).**\n**• Meeting place: Salmon Street Springs fountain plaza\, along SW Naito just north of the Hawthorne Bridge.**\n**• Parking: Recommended parking is at the SmartPark 1st & Jefferson garage (123 SW Jefferson St)\, or nearby downtown street parking if available.**\n**• Restrooms: Downtown/Waterfront options may be available nearby\, but availability can vary—please plan ahead.**\n**• What to bring: Comfortable walking shoes\, layers for spring weather\, water\, snacks\, and a camera/phone for blossom photos.**\n**Notes:**\n**This is a casual\, friendly walk and not a guided tour. Everyone is responsible for their own safety and comfort. We’ll stay together with periodic regroup points\, especially after bridge crossings and in busier sections of the path.**
